1
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,600
Big dummy

2
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:28,120
I'll help you carry it

3
00:01:28,959 --> 00:01:29,760
No need

4
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:31,200
Don't let your mom see you

5
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:32,519
She'll start yelling again

6
00:01:33,680 --> 00:01:34,480
Stop nagging

7
00:01:34,920 --> 00:01:35,439
Hold this

8
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:38,120
Stop nagging

9
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:42,640
Wait a second

10
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,519
You bumped your head

11
00:01:45,519 --> 00:01:46,719
Are you okay?

12
00:01:46,719 --> 00:01:47,719
Slow down

13
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:55,719
The power's out

14
00:01:56,079 --> 00:01:56,840
Wait a moment

15
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,879
I'll get a candle

16
00:02:07,319 --> 00:02:08,120
Let's go

17
00:02:17,919 --> 00:02:18,639
Your family

18
00:02:19,319 --> 00:02:21,199
why do they always make you do this heavy work?

19
00:02:21,719 --> 00:02:23,080
Someone has to do it

20
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:24,879
We're a house full of women

21
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:26,520
and my dad is often on duty

22
00:02:26,719 --> 00:02:28,560
If I don't do it, who will?

23
00:02:33,719 --> 00:02:34,719
You don't need to help

24
00:02:40,039 --> 00:02:41,080
Haven't you been

25
00:02:41,080 --> 00:02:42,520
helping me a bit too much lately?

26
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:46,080
Don't you listen to your mom?

27
00:02:46,719 --> 00:02:47,960
Didn't your mom say

28
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:49,520
we shouldn't hang out?

29
00:03:14,039 --> 00:03:14,960
I...

30
00:03:15,199 --> 00:03:16,120
I'm leaving

31
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:22,680
Does the bump on your head still hurt?

32
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,080
You make me so mad, of course it hurts

33
00:03:28,919 --> 00:03:29,719
Sit down

34
00:03:29,919 --> 00:03:30,719
What for?

35
00:03:53,639 --> 00:03:54,719
Actually

36
00:03:55,319 --> 00:03:57,000
you could stay away from me

37
00:03:58,080 --> 00:04:00,520
Every time you help me, you get unlucky

38
00:04:03,319 --> 00:04:04,719
It's either you don't get promoted

39
00:04:05,039 --> 00:04:06,919
or you get a scolding from your mom

40
00:04:07,919 --> 00:04:10,520
This time you even got a big bump

41
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:15,599
Our families live so close

42
00:04:16,040 --> 00:04:18,000
how can we stay away?

43
00:04:30,639 --> 00:04:31,439
Wang Yingrong

44
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,240
We can only be this close

45
00:04:34,399 --> 00:04:35,279
We can't be far apart

46
00:04:36,519 --> 00:04:37,600
I've thought about it

47
00:04:39,199 --> 00:04:40,079
There's no other way

48
00:04:50,920 --> 00:04:51,720
Yingrong

49
00:04:52,279 --> 00:04:53,319
I bought you a popsicle

50
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:55,120
Thanks for helping carry the rice

51
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,480
Um...

52
00:04:57,480 --> 00:04:59,279
I have things to do, so I'll go now

53
00:04:59,279 --> 00:04:59,879
Sis

54
00:04:59,879 --> 00:05:01,000
He didn't come on purpose

55
00:05:01,319 --> 00:05:02,120
Right, right, right

56
00:05:02,279 --> 00:05:04,120
I was just passing by on my way home

57
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:05,519
You're going home

58
00:05:05,519 --> 00:05:06,920
by passing our house?

59
00:05:27,240 --> 00:05:28,319
Yingrong

60
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:31,680
Why is your face so red?

61
00:05:33,680 --> 00:05:34,240
Sis

62
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:35,720
It's too hot in the room

63
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:37,439
Let's buy a fan later

64
00:05:41,759 --> 00:05:43,360
The budding romance between them

65
00:05:43,360 --> 00:05:44,680
didn't have time to develop

66
00:05:45,279 --> 00:05:47,839
before being put on hold for their careers

67
00:05:49,079 --> 00:05:51,160
Wang Yingrong threw herself into the vinegar workshop

68
00:05:51,759 --> 00:05:54,839
while Acting Factory Manager Zheng Minjiang went to the province

69
00:05:55,079 --> 00:05:56,439
for training and study

70
00:05:57,759 --> 00:05:59,120
Those hidden longings

71
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:01,199
across distance and time

72
00:06:02,399 --> 00:06:03,759
were tethering two hearts

73
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:06,319
brewing the sweetness of the future

74
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:32,360
Come here

75
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,279
You drink it

76
00:06:38,399 --> 00:06:39,480
You... you drink it

77
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:41,839
Drink

78
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:11,079
It worked

79
00:07:23,879 --> 00:07:25,240
So sour

80
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:30,199
It worked

81
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,680
We're amazing

82
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:40,120
I didn't expect

83
00:07:40,120 --> 00:07:42,480
we actually made Baliang Vinegar

84
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:44,000
All this hard work lately

85
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:45,120
wasn't in vain

86
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,680
I knew we could do it

87
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:48,000
Absolutely

88
00:07:48,279 --> 00:07:49,120
I'll go find Big Brother

89
00:07:49,120 --> 00:07:50,519
Let him taste our new vinegar

90
00:07:50,519 --> 00:07:51,879
Why look for Big Brother?

91
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:53,319
Big Brother and Zhen Zhen

92
00:07:53,319 --> 00:07:54,920
went to the province for cadre training

93
00:07:56,079 --> 00:07:56,879
Oh, right

94
00:07:57,199 --> 00:07:58,680
Big Brother has been gone for two months.

95
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,879
Why hasn't he come back yet?

96
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:01,199
But I feel like

97
00:08:01,199 --> 00:08:02,720
after he became the Acting Factory Manager,

98
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,680
he's gotten busier and busier.

99
00:08:04,279 --> 00:08:05,040
It's been months since

100
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:06,319
I've even spoken to him.

101
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:08,279
Without him bossing me around at home,

102
00:08:08,519 --> 00:08:10,000
I'm actually not used to it.

103
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,040
What's with you?

104
00:08:18,399 --> 00:08:19,279
I successfully brewed the vinegar.

105
00:08:19,279 --> 00:08:20,519
Can't I be happy about that?

106
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:22,199
You're happy?

107
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,720
You clearly just miss Big Brother,

108
00:08:25,720 --> 00:08:26,600
but you won't admit it.

109
00:08:26,600 --> 00:08:27,199
Hey!

110
00:08:30,839 --> 00:08:31,240
You...

111
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:31,879
I'm gonna kill you!

112
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,360
Give me a bottle of Baliang Vinegar.

113
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:35,559
I was here first.

114
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:36,519
Okay.

115
00:08:36,519 --> 00:08:38,120
I want Baliang Vinegar too.

116
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,720
I want Baliang Vinegar.

117
00:08:42,879 --> 00:08:44,519
You're always running off somewhere.

118
00:08:44,519 --> 00:08:46,279
Don't you care about things at home?

119
00:08:47,519 --> 00:08:50,120
I just went out to play some chess.

120
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:54,240
We're having wontons for lunch today.

121
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,399
You don't do any work.

122
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:58,440
Hurry up and go buy some Baliang Vinegar.

123
00:08:58,720 --> 00:09:00,080
Baliang Vinegar?

124
00:09:00,480 --> 00:09:03,840
Why does that name sound so familiar?

125
00:09:04,919 --> 00:09:06,720
Isn't that the vinegar

126
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:09,120
that Xu Fugui's sister used to brew?

127
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,600
That's the one.

128
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:13,159
Ever since the trouble with the Xu family,

129
00:09:13,159 --> 00:09:14,759
I haven't had

130
00:09:14,759 --> 00:09:16,480
such fragrant vinegar.

131
00:09:17,279 --> 00:09:18,879
And now we can buy it again.

132
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,639
I heard recently that

133
00:09:21,720 --> 00:09:24,559
the Baliang Vinegar sold on the street sells out instantly.

134
00:09:25,519 --> 00:09:28,039
So who's brewing it now?

135
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:30,080
I heard people say

136
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:31,799
that youngest Wang sister, Wang Yingrong,

137
00:09:31,799 --> 00:09:33,279
is brewing vinegar too.

138
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:34,679
Do you think she's the one making it?

139
00:09:35,399 --> 00:09:37,159
That little girl?

140
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:40,200
Can she really brew that kind of vinegar?

141
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:41,840
Brewing vinegar...

142
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,639
It must be someone with experience.

143
00:09:43,639 --> 00:09:45,960
How could it be the Wangs' second child?

144
00:09:46,200 --> 00:09:46,960
Right, exactly.

145
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:49,240
What's wrong with our Wang family's second child?

146
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,919
You came out just in time.

147
00:09:51,159 --> 00:09:53,879
The vinegar your sister Fugui used to brew...

148
00:09:54,120 --> 00:09:56,720
Is it being brewed again now?

149
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,159
Baliang Vinegar.

150
00:09:58,759 --> 00:10:00,879
Our family hasn't been able to buy it for a long time.

151
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:02,519
Who brewed it this time?

152
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:03,240
Look.

153
00:10:03,440 --> 00:10:04,440
I told you.

154
00:10:04,879 --> 00:10:07,320
Isn't your Yingrong brewing vinegar?

155
00:10:07,440 --> 00:10:09,120
Did she brew...

156
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,240
...her second aunt's Baliang Vinegar?

157
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:13,120
Our Yingrong is young.

158
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:15,120
And she doesn't have any brewing experience.

159
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:17,000
It's impossible.

160
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:18,639
I said it's impossible.

161
00:10:27,279 --> 00:10:28,960
What skills does Second Sister actually have?

162
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,320
To think she could brew good vinegar.

163
00:10:31,559 --> 00:10:33,639
I'd say it's good enough if she doesn't drag the family down.

164
00:10:33,919 --> 00:10:36,039
I don't know what that Yingrong is doing at the vinegar workshop.

165
00:10:36,039 --> 00:10:37,879
What exactly is going on.

166
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,320
Is it that she can't make it...

167
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:40,200
...and lost money?

168
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:41,320
Yingrong is back.

169
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,679
Where did you buy this?

170
00:10:43,679 --> 00:10:44,120
Yeah.

171
00:10:44,120 --> 00:10:45,320
I was just thinking of buying some.

172
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:46,799
Baliang Vinegar.

173
00:10:46,799 --> 00:10:48,039
I got this from Fangfang Restaurant.

174
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,320
Aren't you running a vinegar workshop out there?

175
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:53,080
Didn't you say you brewed it yourself?

176
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,360
And yet you go out to buy it?

177
00:10:54,360 --> 00:10:55,440
I told you not to run a vinegar workshop anymore.

178
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:56,679
Did you even listen to me?

179
00:10:56,679 --> 00:10:58,639
Have you shut down that business out there?

180
00:10:58,639 --> 00:10:59,840
The vinegar has already been brewed.

181
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:01,240
It wouldn't be worth it to close it.

182
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,559
I have to earn some money.

183
00:11:02,559 --> 00:11:03,480
Otherwise, it would all be for nothing.

184
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:05,440
You brewed it?

185
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:06,399
Where is it then?

186
00:11:06,399 --> 00:11:07,600
Why don't I see it?

187
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:08,960
Right here.

188
00:11:10,960 --> 00:11:12,519
Did you see that they're selling well,

189
00:11:12,519 --> 00:11:14,679
and stuck their label on this?

190
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:16,279
Do you take us for fools?

191
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:18,080
You still dare to talk nonsense?

192
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:19,759
Aren't you ashamed of embarrassing yourself?

193
00:11:19,759 --> 00:11:20,200
Let's go.

194
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:20,960
Go home.

195
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,000
I'm not talking nonsense.

196
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:22,720
Exactly.

197
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,360
Second Sister, I think you're crazy for money.

198
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:27,519
Yingrong.

199
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:29,919
Auntie knows you've been hardworking since you were little.

200
00:11:30,080 --> 00:11:32,320
But you have to take things slowly.

201
00:11:32,320 --> 00:11:33,519
There's no need to rush.

202
00:11:33,799 --> 00:11:35,519
Why don't any of you believe me?

203
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:36,799
Here.

204
00:11:36,799 --> 00:11:37,879
Smell this.

205
00:11:48,399 --> 00:11:49,759
It really is Baliang Vinegar.

206
00:11:53,679 --> 00:11:54,919
It smells so good.

207
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:12,960
This is Baliang Vinegar.

208
00:12:13,159 --> 00:12:14,960
You actually brewed your second aunt's vinegar!

209
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:15,720
Impossible.

210
00:12:15,960 --> 00:12:18,000
I don't believe Second Sister could brew it.

211
00:12:18,679 --> 00:12:20,559
Didn't you clearly say just now...

212
00:12:20,559 --> 00:12:22,559
...that you bought it at Fangfang Restaurant?

213
00:12:22,720 --> 00:12:24,559
Do you take us for fools?

214
00:12:24,679 --> 00:12:25,480
Auntie Chen.

215
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:27,879
That I can brew my second aunt's Baliang Vinegar...

216
00:12:27,879 --> 00:12:29,279
...what's so strange about that?

217
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:32,559
If you really brewed it,

218
00:12:32,759 --> 00:12:33,639
then however much we want,

219
00:12:33,639 --> 00:12:34,799
you can provide it, right?

220
00:12:35,399 --> 00:12:36,879
Then bring 100 bottles tomorrow.

221
00:12:37,200 --> 00:12:38,399
And we'll believe you.
